spocs.title: How to Find New Customers and Keep Them Happy
spocs.excerpt: Looking to improve business relationships? See how a CRM solution can help your company stay connected to customers and improve profitability.

recommendations.title: 16 of the highest paid movie roles of all time — including $100 million for a single film
recommendations.excerpt: It's rare for actors to rake in huge salaries today, at least compared to the days when audiences were drawn to a movie primarily based on its leading star.    Years ago, if a certain actor's name was attached to a movie, it was almost a guaranteed success.

recommendations.title: Bojan Krkic: ‘I had anxiety attacks but no one wants to talk about that. Football’s not interested’
recommendations.excerpt: “I have a problem,” Bojan Krkic says, edging forward on the sofa. “I love football, it’s my life.” Outside, through the balcony doors, the sun dips behind Vitoria, northern Spain.

recommendations.title: How to Accept a Compliment
recommendations.excerpt: Ms. Bucior is a writer based in Milwaukee.  Alone in my office one afternoon, I unpeeled the wrapper from a square of chocolate with a deliberate curiosity not associated with office snacking.

recommendations.title: How a Pioneer of Machine Learning Became One of Its Sharpest Critics
recommendations.excerpt: Judea Pearl helped artificial intelligence gain a strong grasp on probability, but laments that it still can't compute cause and effect.  Artificial intelligence owes a lot of its smarts to Judea Pearl. In the 1980s he led efforts that allowed machines to reason probabilistically.

recommendations.title: The End of Male Approval in Comedy
recommendations.excerpt: It’s pure coincidence that Rachel Bloom’s interview on Marc Maron’s WTF aired just three days after Tina Fey’s appearance on David Letterman’s new Netflix show, My Next Guest Needs No Introduction, earlier this month.

recommendations.title: How much the average person in 40 different countries takes home after taxes
recommendations.excerpt: The salary you negotiate isn't the amount you end up receiving in your paychecks. The primary reason: taxes.    It is well known that every country has a different corporate tax rate, but each one also has different tax rates for individuals.

recommendations.title: Michael Pollan: Can Psychedelics Save the World?
recommendations.excerpt: Most people know Michael Pollan as a food writer. His 2006 book, The Omnivore's Dilemma, is widely credited with helping spark the modern food movement, in which everyday Americans began asking questions about where their food comes from.

recommendations.title: Great Things Take Time
recommendations.excerpt: Look at the photo above. See that road in the center that cuts through the mountain ridge? The history behind that road is one of the most remarkable tales of human perseverance, yet you have probably never heard it.

recommendations.title: Apple and Its Rivals Bet Their Futures on These Men’s Dreams
recommendations.excerpt: Over the past five years, artificial intelligence has gone from perennial vaporware to one of the technology industry’s brightest hopes. Computers have learned to recognize faces and objects, understand the spoken word, and translate scores of languages.

recommendations.title: General Thinking Tools: 9 Mental Models to Solve Difficult Problems
recommendations.excerpt: When I came across Charlie Munger’s 1995 Speech, The Psychology of Human Misjudgment, I realized that I could learn more from him than my MBA. So I spent the next few years reading and researching about cognitive biases and how we mislead ourselves.

recommendations.title: Inside Mueller’s FBI team
recommendations.excerpt: President Donald Trump has repeatedly hurled insults at the FBI agents working on special counsel Robert Mueller’s investigation into the 2016 campaign. Rudy Giuliani, a former U.S. attorney who’s now Trump’s lawyer, has attacked them as “stormtroopers.”  The vitriol is unsurprising.

recommendations.title: 10 Most Breathtaking Day Hikes in the U.S.
recommendations.excerpt: The United States is home to some of the most diverse landscapes on the planet, ranging from barren deserts and vast canyons to lush forests and snow-capped mountains. Because of this, it's no surprise that it also has some of the most spectacular and accessible hiking trails in the world.

recommendations.title: Did You Know There Are 5 Levels of Listening?
recommendations.excerpt: Most people who think they are good listeners underperform. There is some research that suggests they do so by as much as 60%. This overconfidence impedes their success as it prevents them from truly understanding the motivation of the other side.

recommendations.title: Steven Pinker’s Ideas About Progress Are Fatally Flawed. These Eight Graphs Show Why.
recommendations.excerpt: It’s time to reclaim the mantle of “Progress” for progressives. By falsely tethering the concept of progress to free market economics and centrist values, Steven Pinker has tried to appropriate a great idea for which he has no rightful claim.

recommendations.title: Find out how much car you can afford with 20/4/10 rule
recommendations.excerpt: Knowing how much car you can afford is the first step to buying one.  Also, water is wet.

recommendations.title: Transform Your Life By Transforming Your Habits
recommendations.excerpt: Where you are in your life is a result of your habits. Will Durant (not Aristotle) said it best:  I think that’s also true for the opposite of excellence. Mediocrity is a result of mediocre habits.

recommendations.title: Lawns Are an Ecological Disaster
recommendations.excerpt: Neil Tyson often conjectures that maybe aliens have concluded humans aren’t intelligent enough to contact. He’s probably referring to our capacity for war, but lawns may display our talent for fruitless carnage even better.

recommendations.title: 'I felt exposed online': how to disappear from the internet
recommendations.excerpt: Worried about what’s out there about you? You’re not alone. But is it even possible to become a digital ghost?

recommendations.title: The decline of Snapchat and the secret joy of internet ghost towns
recommendations.excerpt: It’s difficult to believe now, but there was a time when the internet was nowhere instead of everywhere.

recommendations.title: Cannes Interview: Christopher Nolan
recommendations.excerpt: Though he’s still never been invited to present one of his own films at the festival, Christopher Nolan became the center of attention during the first weekend of Cannes this year.
